ffordable, inclusive, and equitable cities? While many books dwell on the analysis of problems, Reimagining Sustainable Cities prioritizes solutions-oriented thinking—surveying historical trends, providing examples of constructive action worldwide, and outlining alternative problem-solving strategies. Wheeler and Rosan use a social ecology lens and draw perspectives from multiple disciplines. Positive, readable, and constructive in tone, Reimagining Sustainable Cities identifies actions ranging from urban design to institutional restructuring that can bring about fundamental change and prepare us for the challenges ahead.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aCity planningxEnvironmental aspects. 0aCity planningxSocial aspects. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology) 0aUrban ecology (Sociology). 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520381209zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520381209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520381209/original  a978-3-11-073915-2  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles